(177, 97, 172, 11, 'RE: Hero idea', 0, 78, 'DJackal', 1383482437, 'I''ll do a quick run down of your hero. First of all, he is incredibly overpowered, with the ability to be invulnerable for almost the whole game. Also, you''re forcing the player to level up the first skill immediately (since all his spells revolves around it), which can severely prevent any other playstyles for the hero.\r\n\r\nHis first skill is just unfair, adding invulnerability to the hero as long as the minion is alive. I would just tuck the minion somewhere safe and abuse my invulnerability. You should just make the minion something that is with him at the start of the game, perhaps in the form of an Innate Passive.\r\n\r\nSecond skill lasts too long for a duration. 6 seconds is just plain unforgiving for both a slow and a damage modifier. Good synergy, but its just too long.\r\n\r\nFor the third skill, while this has good synergy with the first skill, but again can easily be abused to the first skills invulnerability.\r\n\r\nFor the last skill, he already has a hard sustain. No need for another one. I''d suggest making this more of a supportive spell for team fights or an actual damage spell, since he doesn''t have any. Else, make it a sort of deflect spell, to make his enemies be damaged (whether in HP or not) when they try to smack him.', '182.18.223.160', -1240277088, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
(179, 97, 178, 11, 'RE: Hero idea', 0, 78, 'DJackal', 1383569524, '[quote=''Chaosy'' pid=''178'' dateline=''1383489792'']\r\nedited skills 1 and 4.\r\n\r\nfor spell 2 you can change values any time you want. I just want the concept of such an hero.\r\n\r\nspell 3: I disagree. But its hard to say Before you see the hero in action.\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nStill, it would be a lot better if you just removed hero invulnerability and but remove the requires to be at a certain range part. This allows for a dual play style, say the minion farms at the jungle then the hero goes at the lane. This adds depth to the hero.\r\n\r\nYou just really need 1 self-support (in this case healing) spell for a hero. You can get away with two, but make sure they are not of different magnitudes. This gives bad counter-play and makes the hero pretty much dominate. Just remove the healing part and perhaps keep the damage bonus and make the stun say half a second and remove 15% of the hero''s health.\r\n\r\nBuff-stacking is inherently not a bad idea as long as you both display it and cap it. Perhaps add a cap if you really want that healing part to prevent too much buffs. This cap can be increased by say leveling up the 3rd skill.\r\n\r\nI think Sion from League of Legends is a very similar hero to this mechanics wise and you should look on how he is implemented.', '182.18.223.69', -1240277179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
