(68, 62, 0, 11, 'Qar''tha the Psychologist', 0, 21, 'Lindo', 1335098173, '[img]http://www.wowpedia.org/images/6/69/BTNPriest.png[/img]\r\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Psychologist[/color][/b]\r\n[color=#9400D3]Qar''tha[/color]\r\n\r\n[color=#006400]Description:[/color]\r\nQar''tha is a full support hero. With his magic, he can change all his enemies'' mind and destroy their bodies systems. He prevents all enemies to escape from the war and he never lets his enemy who has fast movespeed to run away.\r\n\r\n[color=#006400]Background Story:[/color]\r\n\r\nQar''tha has studied psychology for 5 years. He was a good lecturer. But he is not only a usual psychologist. He hast mystical staff which can change his enemies mind. He has joined in Magic Sentrum for 3 years.\r\n\r\nQar''tha learned all psychology very well. He learned how to control others mind. All people said that Qartha was the best psychologist. He got the staff when he went to Magic Sentrum. he learned magic and spell. Then he combined both magic and his knowledge about psychology. He was the one who only could change others mind and destroy their bodies systems very well. He became an assistant of Magic Sentrum Leader. He taught the others about psychology and how to use it in good situation.\r\n\r\nNow, he leaves the Magic Sentrum and joins a war. He helps all the warriors to kill enemies. He uses his magic and spell to changes all enemies'' mind. He is not only a psychologist or psychiatrist. He is a Mind Destroyer.\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/6/65/Priest.gif[/IMG]\r\n[color=#1E90FF]Strength - 12 + [2.1][/color]\r\n[color=#1E90FF]Agility - 20 + [1.6][/color]\r\n[color=#FF4500]Intelligence - 27 + [2.8][/color]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.playdota.com/img/site/as.gif[/img]\r\nAffiliation:Sentinel\r\nDamage:42-50\r\nArmor:2.86\r\nMovespeed:295\r\nStarting HP/MP:378/351\r\nAttack Range:600\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.playdota.com/img/site/sk.gif[/img]\r\n\r\n[img]http://images2.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20090228100048/wowwiki/images/e/e3/Inv_essenceofwintergrasp.png[/img]\r\n[color=#1E90FF][b]BUILDING PSYCHIC[/b][/color]\r\nQar''tha blinds enemy''s mind. Enemy gains bonus damage and goes to nearby building in 375 AoE. The enemy attacks the building for 4 times. Afterward this buff is finished.\r\nLevel 1 --- Gain 7 bonus damage\r\nLevel 2 --- Gain 14 bonus damage\r\nLevel 3 --- Gain 21 bonus damage\r\nLevel 4 --- Gain 28 bonus damage\r\n\r\nManacost : 120/130/140/150\r\nCooldown : 20\r\nCasting Range : 700\r\nAoE : 375\r\n\r\nNB:\r\n-The enemy attacks his base building\r\n-When the target doesn''t find any building in 375 AoE, this buff disappears.\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://images1.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20070113175559/wowwiki/images/f/ff/Spell_arcane_focusedpower.png[/img]\r\n[color=#1E90FF][b]PSYCHO EXCHANGE[/b][/color]\r\nThe Psychologist exchange the enemies hero in 425 AoE. Their control are swapped each other and unable to cast a spell more than once[/table]\r\nLevel 1 --- Last 4 seconds\r\nLevel 2 --- Last 5 seconds\r\nLevel 3 --- Last 6 seconds\r\nLevel 4 --- Last 7 seconds\r\n\r\nManacost : 100/110/120/130\r\nCooldown : 16\r\nCasting Range : 500\r\nAoE : 425\r\n\r\nNB:\r\n-When the enemies has casted a spell, they will be silent until this buff is finished\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://images3.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20061125005240/wowwiki/images/9/93/Spell_fire_flamebolt.png[/img]\r\n[color=#1E90FF][b]PSYCHOLOGY BLAST[/b][/color]\r\nThe Psychologist shoots a psychology blast. Deals damage base on enemy MS. Give ministun for 0.1 second.\r\nLevel 1 --- Deals 35% of MS\r\nLevel 2 --- Deals 50% of MS\r\nLevel 3 --- Deals 65% of MS\r\nLevel 4 --- Deals 80% of MS\r\n\r\nManacost : 100/130/160/190\r\nCooldown : 12/10/8/6\r\nCasting Range : 700\r\n\r\nNB:\r\n-Deals base on  MAX movespeed\r\n-When the target''s MS is slowed, it will not reduce this dealing damage\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://images3.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20060923092838/wowwiki/images/2/24/Spell_holy_spiritualguidence.png[/img]\r\n[color=#FF4500][b]PSYCHOLOGICAL WARFARE[/b][/color]\r\nQar''tha changes all enemies hero into nervous and non-normality. They move in opposite of the pointed area. Forward to Backward, Backward to Forward, Left to Right and Right to Left. Slows their movespeed by 15%.\r\nLevel 1 --- Last 3 seconds\r\nLevel 2 --- Last 4 seconds\r\nLevel 3 --- Last 5 seconds\r\n\r\nManacost : 275/375/475\r\nCooldown : 160/155/150\r\nCasting Range : Global', '180.251.66.126', -1258601858, 1, 0, 21, 1335161943, 1, '4eda5e0a1c13d45dc6452bc884d4c87d', '', 0),
(69, 62, 68, 11, 'RE: Qar''tha the Psychologist', 0, 4, 'Alien@System', 1335113130, 'I appreciate the suggestion, and this seems to be both a bit thought over and actually realizable within the constraints of warcraft. It is also not overpowered and the spells are not inherently unbalanceable.\r\nAlthough there are two things I have to complain about:\r\nThis hero basically has the target to confuse the enemy, criplle his offensive power and screw up the control. We have someone like this [url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/master-banshee]already[/url], and I tell you, order screws are difficult to trigger and lose their effectiveness as soon as you know they exist.\r\nAnd then there is the matter of Theme. I don''t know why people try to create a hero that is something mundane made "awesome". Psychologist? Sorry, but that is just like "Cohen and the mad Dentists", "Haxxor, the Computer Nerd" (seen a suggestion for him actually) or "The Night elf that failed being a Sorceress" (not made up). Aim a bit higher people! You are suggesting persons that are meant to punch out the Lich-King. They were chosen for being the best, so they should be heroic, not some barber who lost his brother to the Undead. Call him a Trickster, or Reality Warper, or Mindflayer, not Psychologist! Those heroes represent the cream of the crop! Give me a demon-hunter who is cooler than Illidan! A Warden that is more obsessed than Maiev! A Pitlord who can Curb-Stomp Mannoroth!!\r\nIt''s not that difficult. Just be a bit more creative, and look for synonyms when figuring out the spell names.\r\nPS: Please remember that DotU has a slightly different Gameplay. Normal Spells have 5 Levels, Ultimates 3, and the Hero is not representing and indicidual, but a class and the two Sides are named Undead and Alliance (which is split into Human, Orc, Night Elf and Neutral)', '141.30.246.185', -1927350599, 1, 0, 4, 1335117539, 1, '3222cdb521edb1eb00ff7f26587ca879', '', 0),
(70, 63, 0, 7, 'A Basic Guide to Undead Heroes', 0, 4, 'Alien@System', 1335125002, 'As I have often seen people leave the game because they could not understand their hero, and skilled him wrong, I''ll give you a basic introduction into the different heroes and for what player group it is meant. It is much theorycraft, but should give you the basic direction\r\n\r\n[size=large][b][color=#FFA500][u]Easy Heroes[/u][/color][/b][/size]\r\n\r\n[b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/behemot]Behemot[/url][/b], as all-around tank, is probably one of the easier characters. He has high Hit Points, decent movement speed and can punch quite well. Unlike other heroes, all three of his skills can work as first skills (although Roar is not as strong as the other two).\r\nAs he is a front row hero, he should be polstered with armor, health and strength items. His job is to kill Creeps. While he can kill heroes, he is not the fastest and lacks a good skill to keep heroes bound to him, as he knocks everything back, meaning farther away from himself. This ability to mix up the battlefield can save his life, as he can break up surrounds or (in extreme cases) also flee copletely using his Ultimate.\r\n\r\nThe [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/ice-avatar]Ice Avatar[/url][/b], in contrast to my expectations, seems to be one of the easier casters, although he actually is forced to go into melee often. That may be due to the fact that his main skill is also his first skill, so even tl;dr players end up skilling him right. \r\nThe Ice Avatar is surviving by being dangerous. He has not much health and could easily be stomped into the ground by other melee heroes, but getting close is often suicidal, as the good Icy Ghost player can rip a hero to shreds with the Ice Tornado and prevent them from fleeing by slowing them down to a crawl with Freezing breath. It is nonetheless advised to pick up some health items to make the use of the Ultimate succesful, since the 50% evasion will not save you from a whole army.\r\n\r\n[b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/master-banshee]Master Banshees[/url][/b] are pretty straightforward in both skill pick and playstile. The first ability, Dark Confusion, is also the main skill that can render whole armies useless and annoy enemy heroes to a large extend.\r\nThe Banshee should stay in the back row and avoid trouble, but also cause as much as possible. Nearly no other hero has, while limited damage, so much annoyance potential. One thing one should take note of is that a banished hero cannot take physical damage, so coordinate with your hero-killer to prevent anger. Item-build should be clearly focused on mana, and escape items should be preferred over health (the banshee can deal much damage just with hit and run tactics).\r\n\r\nThe [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/dark-ranger]Dark Ranger[/url][/b] is a very specialised hero-hunter. Unless you try to play her as a Slayer, not much can go wrong. Main Skill in her case is Snipe, which is the bane of every hero on the battlefield: (Nearly) inescapable damage over great distances. The other two abilities should be skilled equally, as they both make chasing much easier. Ghost Form, the weaker of the two is also very good for escape.\r\nItembuild should be mostly damage and speed, but a bit of health can''t hurt, as sometimes the hunted may turn around, and being squishy in this case can be lethal.\r\n\r\n[align=left][attachment=6][attachment=7][attachment=8][/align]\r\n\r\n[size=large][b][color=#FFA500][u]Medium Heroes[/u][/color][/b][/size]\r\n\r\nThe [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/death-marcher]Death Marcher[/url][/b] could be an easy hero, if not for his Mana Concentration, that, while being very dangerous, can be his death when used wrong. Main skill is first skill, Death Pact. It should be practically spammed, as it is a real life-saver for anyone but the sacrifice. (The sacrifice should be a summoned skeleton in the early game and a skeleton brute in the mid game. Spawned units should be preferred over preplaced units, as the former die at the end of the rounfd anyway)\r\nItem build is clear: Health, strength, armor to survive, and a bit of mana to make Mana Concentration more effective.\r\n\r\n[b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/skeleton-mage]Skeleton Mage[/url][/b] is effective, as long as the skills are chosen right. Spawn Zombie should be the spell of choice, as it gives you instant minions with a vicious DoT around them. The do not even require a corpse to spawn from. Second skill is the Soul Extraction, which will increase the damage output of both you hero and your zombies.\r\nThe Ultimate is a bit tricky to read. It needs corpses to function, or, if there aren''t any around, it can be cast on your Zombies. Item build should be mana, but since you''ll be not the one dealing damage, you can do your supporter a favior and also bring some supportive Items (like Auras) along.\r\n\r\nA [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/nerubian-widow]Nerubian Widow[/url][/b] is, in terms of raw damage, even a bit better than a Dark Ranger, but is more difficult to play, as the skills all require either patience or good timing. The first skill should be adolescense, which allows you to summon smaller spiders to your side. Catch: they start small, with low hit points and not much damage. To bring them to full potential, they have to grow, which happens slowly. So make some before the round starts, or enemy ranged units will have an easy job crippling your damage output. When hunting, rely on the web and items to get to your target. Sprint will drain your mana quickly, so use it only when you are sure to catch you enemy. And switch it off when you reach it.\r\nItem build? Damage and speed of course, with health and mana about equally as second picks.\r\n\r\n[align=left][attachment=9][attachment=10][attachment=11][/align]\r\n\r\n[size=large][b][color=#FFA500][u]Hard Heroes[/u][/color][/b][/size]\r\n\r\nThe [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/master-necromancer]Master Necromancer[/url][/b] is the hero who fits the definition of "glass cannon" best. He is very easy to kill, but in return can destroy a whole army without even breaking in sweat. His main skill is his first skill (strangely, no one seems to notice. The most common picked skill seems to be Dark Spirit, which is the most difficult). The Skeletons are stronger than the Zombies of his malnourished counterpart and can provide a very good meat, sorry, bone shield. His second skill should be Malicious Curse, which should be switched to health constantly. It deals a lot of damage to a large group and should be cast on units that will stay on the battlefield for a while (but not on the best, as the curse will not damage the target itself).\r\nDark Spirit, last in the line, is good when a hero tries to flee and the hunter isn''t around. It''ll deal damage to the enemy when he moves but also make him invulnerable to all other damage. So it has no use on the battlefield itself, but can out down those guys who want to flee when the health bar turns slightly red.\r\nYes, the Ultimate is passive and only triggers on death. But posthumous Vengeance is strong and kills by percentage, forcing even a tank down in no time. And, as mentioned, you''ll die a lot.\r\nItem build should include mana of course, but as he is very squishy, one should also pick up a bit of defense and movement speed.\r\n\r\nAaah, [b][url=http://playdotu.com/heroes/dread-lord]Dread Lord[/url][/b]. The backbone of the Undead Army, able to get a distressed hero to full health in no time. Able to grant infinite mana. Able to put all those annoying do-gooders to sleep. Able to slay- No, unfortunately not. The Dread Lord is the best support you could ever find. But he can''t deal damage. That makes him probably the most hated useful character in the game. No one wants to play him, but I promise: play him right, and everybody will love you.\r\nMain skill is Purify. Max it out as soon as possible, and spam it. Especially the later levels are able to keep a tank alive even when focused. Don''t forget to heal yourself from time to time. You''re of no use when dead.\r\nThe Vampire blood can relieve your poor W key a bit, as it makes the units able to heal themselves. Focus it on you tanks, of course. Ask them to come to you before the battle if neccessary, as hitting them in the crowd is a matter of luck.\r\nThe Sleepy Dust is nice to annoy your enemy, as those things can stay for quite a while, effectively forming a minefield. It''s difficult to get them to hit an intended target, but careful placement can win the day. Place them for example in Areas where a no Creep walks normally (like the forest paths), or where a single sleeping unit can block a lot (North and South of the Northern/southern defense tower in the forward base, in the bottleneck in the ford, or the one at the end of the lower forest lane)\r\nYour Ultimate, Night Dome is caster heaven. Unlimited Mana for a long time, and the enemies loose additional mana when they cast. It requires a stationary front, though. If you''re forced out of it, the high mana invested into it is wasted. \r\nItem build: Health and Mana. Yes, in that order. You''ll find yourself closer to the action than you''ll like, so grab some armor.', '141.30.246.185', -1927350599, 1, 0, 1, 1378801714, 1, 'c867c5de103c62e4af9385f0f602a060', '', 0),
