(78, 67, 0, 11, 'Hero Idea Bundles', 0, 0, 'S[ub]lime', 1335266341, 'Hey guys! From now on, I will be constantly updating this thread and fill it with hero ideas. Even if it may/may not be accepted, I will still post! These ideas are meant for this project and it only, so please dont use it for your map. If you ever need, visit my Hiveworkshop Account and check my Units Ideas Factory!\n\n[align=center][font=Trebuchet MS][size=large][b][color=#FFff00]Tjol Whitepaw, Drunken Brawler - AGI(Tank/Support)[/b][/size][/color]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Suggested Model/s:[/color][/b] Pandaren Brewmaster\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Description:[/color][/b] A Hero based roughly on his abilities to increase his melee damage. Even if though he is a Tank, he is squishy without Supports nearby. Relies on his melee capabilities. You would need some items which would boost his mana to make him a better hero.\n[color=#32CD32][b]Battle Stats:[/b][/color]\nAttack: 35 - 42\nBase Armor: 3\nAgility: 22 + 2.3\nInteligence: 10 + 1.1\nStrength: 18 + 1.6\n[b][color=#32CD32]Speed:[/color][/b] \nAttack Speed: Medium\nMovement Speed: Medium\n[color=#32CD32][b]Abilities:[/b][/color]\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/6/61/BTNStrongDrink.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]1. Ale of Quick Feet - No Target[/color][/b]\nThe next consumable which Tjol will use would be infused with Ale, which excites him, making him faster and stronger. Tjol would also miss most of his attacks because he is Drunk. The accuracy reduction depends on the number of times he casted this spell x seconds before. \n\nAttacked units get a Beer Buff.\n\n[url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btncr_goblin_chemical_spill-57411/][img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/4/icons_3383_btn.jpg[/img][/url]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]2. Beer Spill - Area Target[/color][/b]\nActive Effect: Tjol scatters beer all over the target area, giving all units Beer Buffs. Costs a moderate amount of mana.\n\nPassive Effect: Beer Buffs excite Tjol and make him do stronger damage to the affected unit/s. Beer Buffs lasts for a moderate amount of time and can stack up to 3 times. Tjol may also stun units with Beer Buffs for a short amount of time.\n\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/5/58/BTNDrunkenDodge.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]3. Drunken Fist - On/Off Target[/color][/b]\nTjol consumes numerous amounts of Ale, stunning him for a few seconds after activation. After, he enters Drunken Mode. It makes him faster, stronger and better chance of dodging attacks. During this mode, his accuracy is lowered by a moderate amount.\n\nIf he casts a spell during this mode, it is cancelled. Drains a few mana every second. Attacked units get a Beer Buff.\n\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Ultimate:[/color][/b]\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/5/50/BTNFire.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]4. Fireplay - No Target[/color][/b]\nTjol drinks a beer which ignites his weapon, giving him a red skin, that of a Fire Panda. Each of Tjol''s attacks would be packed with flames, making all units with Beer Buffs take damage per second. It would burn them until the buffs were off. Lasts for a long duration. Costs a huge amount of mana.\n\nUnits with Beer Buffs may also be damaged by other fire spells.\n\n[/align][/font]', '14.116.116.124', 242513020, 1, 0, 22, 1335400315, 1, '411c27b35c8dd775106136823e43169e', '', 0),
