(87, 67, 78, 11, 'RE: Hero Idea Bundles', 0, 0, 'S[ub]lime', 1335332978, 'I dont know if theres a double posting rule here but meh.\nNew one:\n\n[align=center][font=Trebuchet MS][size=large][b][color=#FFff00]Lorgar Hawkeye, Holy Swashbuckler - AGI(Support/Carry)[/b][/size][/color]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Suggested Model/s:[/color][/b] http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/models-530/roman-glorious-witch-hunter-147330/\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Description:[/color][/b] Good ranged hero. Specializes at far attacks and initiating attacks. Also can switch to melee mode, which allows him to do more damage. Overall balanced/good hero. Yet, he only is good when grouped and late game. Difficult to master. Relies on items and his ultimate ability. When in ranged mode, he is this hero who attacks from great distances. When melee, he is this Debuffer.\n\n[color=#32CD32][b]Battle Stats:[/b][/color]\nAttack: 37 - 44/30 - 39\nBase Armor: 5/7\nAgility: 22 + 2\nInteligence: 22 + 1.8\nStrength: 8 + 1.15\n[b][color=#32CD32]Speed:[/color][/b] \nAttack Speed: Slow\nMovement Speed: Medium\n[color=#32CD32][b]Abilities:[/b][/color]\n\n[b][color=#32CD32]Ranged Abilities:[/color][/b]\n\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/1/1b/BTNFragmentationBombs.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]1. Scattershot - No Target[/color][/b]\nFires a number of bullets in different directions, dealing damage to any unit the projectile hits. Deals minimal damage.\n\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/e/ee/BTNHumanMissileUpOne.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]2. Bullet of Light - No Target[/color][/b]\nActive Effect: A Holy Bullet which dispels undead units are used on Lorgars next strike. It may deal moderate damage to an undead unit or remove a friendly allied unit of all its negative buffs.\n\nPassive Effect: Lorgar may place holy energy on his gun, making the next strike stronger. It may deal moderate bonus damage and would deal stronger damage if fighting an undead unit.\n\n[url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btntakeaim-183540/][img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/13/icons_12788_pas.jpg[/img][/url]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]3. Precision Strikes - Passive[/color][/b]\nLorgar modifies his rifles with special items in order to increase his range. Increases his attack range by a moderate amount and the sight range by a moderate amount as well.\n\n[b][color=#32CD32]Melee Abilities:[/color][/b]\n\n[img]http://images.wikia.com/wowwiki/images/3/30/BTNArcaniteMelee.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]1. Nega-Drain - Unit Target[/color][/b]\nCloaks his blade with holy energy and strikes the target unit. If the target is:\n- An ally, he drains all buffs. He gets all negative buffs and takes x damage from them. But, when he gets a positive buff, he gets x bonus movement and attack speed.\n- An enemy, he prolongs the duration of all negative buffs, doubling their duration and dealing minimal damage.\n- An enemy undead unit, he deals larger damage and damages the target unit more depending on the number of buffs.\n\n[img]http://images3.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20090111213552/wowwiki/images/5/56/BTNBarkSkin.png[/img]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]2. Magic Shell - Unit Target[/color][/b]\nCreates a shell of holy magic at the target unit. This makes all Negative Buffs be reflected and be tossed to the nearest enemy unit. Costs x mana for Lorgar. A bond is created with the two units, if either unit goes too far from each other, the bond will break, so as the Magic Shell.\n\n[url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btnalliance-192499/][img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/14/icons_13427_pas.jpg[/img][/url]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]3. Bonds! - Passive[/color][/b]\nLorgar sends out an energy from himself and creates a link between nearby allied units. This link dispels all buffs and splits the damage they take from enemy units, depending on the units affected. The link is broken when going too far. The link also shares their positive buffs, but make it last shorter, also depending on the number of units affected. Spells casted by the affected units would be stronger, depending on the number of affected units.\n\n[b][color=#1E90FF]Ultimate:[/color][/b]\n[url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btncrweaponswitch-112046/][img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/7/icons_6375_btn.jpg[/img][/url]\n[b][color=#1E90FF]4. Weapon Exchange - No Target[/color][/b]\nLorgar switches his weapon, making him a Melee Hero if he has his gun or a Ranged Hero when his blade is equipped. All Abilities switch their effects once they are switched.\n\nNote: No Mana Cost, High Cooldown\n\n[/align][/font]', '113.103.135.51', 1902610227, 1, 0, 22, 1335400301, 1, '927abf10648b4becdd2afcbc2ae81be6', '', 0),
(94, 67, 78, 11, 'RE: Hero Idea Bundles', 0, 4, 'Alien@System', 1335366087, 'The Drunken Brawler would be very difficult to balance due to the lack of Mana. (People probably would ask why he has an Intelligence score then and if he hasn''t, why he gains less Attributes per level than other heroes). And the Ultimate would collide with the other Panda in our Map, which is actually a Fire Panda.\r\n\r\nCreating a Morphing Hero who has different skill sets clashes with the engine, both that of warcraft and our own triggers. And I''m not really in favor of the model. It looks good, but since Gen. Frank is merging animations, it moves funny.', '141.30.246.182', -1927350602, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '37b4d9019397f8621725988031b8cf5a', '', 0),
