(189, 102, 0, 11, 'The Night Angel', 0, 4, 'Alien@System', 1384028579, '[align=center][attachment=16]\r\n[size=large]The Night Angel[/size]\r\nWhile the Priestess of the Moon represents the benevolent aspect of the Moon Goddess, the Night Angel is an embodiment of Her wrath. With no name, no past and a single cause, the Night Angel is the most feared assassin, cleaning the world of sinners. Her movements unforseeable, her methods unorthodox and her combination of skill and magic unsurpassable, any target she chooses finds a swift and painful death.[/align]\r\n\r\n[align=center][size=medium]Skills[/size][/align]\r\n[img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/9/icons_8486_btn.jpg[/img]([url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btnchainblade-138863/]Link[/url])\r\n[b]Grappling Chain[/b]\r\nThe Night Angel shoots a chain at a target, pulling herself to heroes or non-hero units to herself. While the chain is attached, enemy heroes are slowed by 50% and non-hero units are stunned.\r\n\r\n[img]http://classic.battle.net/war3/images/nightelf/spells/shadowstrike.gif[/img]\r\n[b]Moon Blade[/b]\r\nThe Night Angel throws her chakram at the target location, then returns to her, slightly damaging all enemy units in its path and increasing the damage they receive from the Night Angel or Midnight Seraph for 20 seconds. While the blade flies, the Night Angel cannot attack normally.\r\n[img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/11/icons_10307_btn.jpg[/img]([url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btnwardenglaive-154942/]Link[/url])\r\n[b]Redirect[/b]\r\n[i]This replaces Moon Blade while the chakram is flying.[/i]\r\nThe Night Angel magically alters the trajectory of her chakram to fly towards a new location. Using this spell extends the flight time of the Moon Blade. It costs less mana than Moon Blade and has no cooldown.\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/resource_images/13/icons_12797_btn.jpg[/img]([url=http://www.hiveworkshop.com/forums/icons-541/btnpoisonaura-183615/]Link[/url])\r\n[b]Nightshade[/b]\r\nThe Night Angel poisons the target with a subtle, slowly killing poison. For 15 seconds, the target takes a small amount of damage per second. Whenever they are damaged by the Night Angel or Midnight Seraph, the DoT increases by 100% for three ticks and the target is slowed for three seconds.\r\n\r\n[img]http://classic.battle.net/war3/images/nightelf/spells/spiritofvengeance.gif[/img]\r\n[b]Midnight Seraph[/b]\r\nThe Night Angel summons an avatar of her religious fury that is even more relentless in her hunt than herself. The Midnight Seraph is untargetable, uncontrollable and can move through units. She attacks targets the Night Angel is ordered to attack, and whenever the Night Angel casts a spell, the Seraph is instantly transported to the target location (For the unit target spells, she also begins attacking that target). The Seraph lasts for a certain time or until she gets too far away from the Night Angel.\r\n\r\n[size=medium]Concept[/size]\r\nThe Night Angel is meant as a fast-paced, slightly challenging Hero Hunter, the first the Alliance would get. This way, not only the Alliance Heroes now have to fear to get suddenly sliced to pieces while they try to flee.\r\nHer mobility spell is obviously Grappling Hook, which allows her to quickly get into or out of the fray, and to catch up with fleeing heroes. It works against both enemies and friends, allowing her to move back as well. The catch: It only works against heroes. When there''s none around, the Night Angel is restricted to using her feet.\r\nMoon Blade and Nightshade provide her important damage buffs. They deal only low damage on their own, so all damage that is dealt has to be dealt as weapon damage. And the Night Shade is a melee fighter, so there''s no way to get around to exposing your hide by jumping over to the enemy lines. While Moon Blade gives her a bit of ammunition against several targets, Nightshade forces the single-target playstyle on her. Unless you''re hitting the target, the poison doesn''t do much.\r\nRedirect is mostly a gimmick, although it is also meant as frustration-preventer: When your target dodges the first throw, just get it with an unexpected course change. The damage buff also affects itself, so redirecting the blade over a target hit before results in bonus damage. Again, there''s a rather large catch: While the blade flies, you can''t attack. Your only options are to use spells, or to wait until it comes back. So you might not want to spam Redirect (which is also a great way to completely drain your mana) and if you''re in a hurry, maybe even jump after your chakram with the Grappling Chain.\r\nThe Ultimate is another damage increase which allows you to give your tired arms a bit of a rest, as the Seraph can hunt targets for you. Problem is the limited range, which makes retreating a very well-working tactic when faced with a Seraph without her Night Angel nearby.\r\nThe main weakness of the hero: Low Health. Except for getting the heck out of there with Grappling Chain, there is no way to escape damage directed at you.', '77.179.204.182', 1303628982, 1, 0, 4, 1384028615, 1, '', '', 0),
