(185, 97, 183, 11, 'RE: Hero idea', 0, 77, 'Chaosy', 1383694356, '[quote=''Alien@System'' pid=''183'' dateline=''1383672483'']\r\nI have to agree, the invulnerability is ... ugly. There has to be a window in which the hero is actually vulnerable, and you''d need a rather extreme cooldown to provide that. And it''d still be a "Get out of Jail Free" card. When you''re low on health and hunted, just summon the thing and bolt - in the time the hunter kills your minion, you''re out of danger. If I''d assign the skill, I''d use it as ultimate, with a cooldown of 120 seconds or longer. Invulnerability timed like that is just too strong.\r\n\r\nWhen playing this hero, I''d skip Haunt, simply because it''s so much stronger to have the minion out and keep it on the sidelines for the continued invulnerability.\r\n\r\nAbout skill 3 and 4, let me at first say that I dislike skills messing around with base stats permanently. It becomes a PITA to balance. For an ultimate, the effect of the last skill also seems rather weak.\r\n\r\nI also don''t see the tanking aspect of the hero. He''s invulnerable, there''s no need to add health, I''d just go for damage spam.\r\n\r\nOh, and looks like pred managed to overlook a small detail: We do already have a hero that summons minions, collects souls and unleashes them for more effect. He also looks like a skeleton. And has a skill that''s a slightly slowing and damaging bebuff.\r\n\r\nPS: To my latest knowledge, we don''t have jungling.\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\ntoo much "hate" on this idea so I will thrash it. Thanks for all the critism', '84.217.49.40', 1423520040, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
(200, 112, 0, 12, 'Help & Support Forum Rules', 0, 1, 'pred1980', 1384348484, 'In addition to the [url=http://forsaken-bastions-fall.com/forums/Announcement-Global-Forum-Rules]Global Forum Rules[/url], the following rules apply to the Help & Support section.\r\n[list=1]\r\n[*]The purpose of this forum is for new members to ask non-gameplay support questions. Please be very specific and descriptive in your questioning.\r\n[*]This is not a forum in regards to gameplay. Gameplay support and discussion should be found in [url=http://forsaken-bastions-fall.com/forums/Forum-FBF-Chat]FBF Chat[/url] and [url=http://forsaken-bastions-fall.com/forums/Forum-Guides-Strategy]Guides & Strategy[/url].\r\n[*]When posting and answering questions, please be very kind and user-friendly. Tolerance to new members is expected.\r\n[/list]\r\n\r\n ', '94.101.33.114', 1583686002, 0, 0, 1, 1384352206, 1, '', '', 1),
(201, 102, 189, 11, 'RE: The Night Angel', 0, 78, 'DJackal', 1384835503, 'A nice hero there. Although I have a few suggestions (mostly coming from an AoS standpoint):\r\n- 50% slow could be lessened to something like 10 - 20%. The units are already pulled to her, so she doesn''t need a greater effect for positioning. You could have that 50% slow if you shrunk its duration to half a second to 1.5 seconds.\r\n- 20 seconds could be like 10 seconds or 15 seconds max.\r\n- I find the DoT duration too long and the damage increase too high. Say 3 - 7 seconds with a 25 - 35% increase is fine.\r\n- The ultimate plays well, but I''m not sure with the teleport thing. It can really mess up her positioning. Say the Night Angel is attacking a unit, casts a spell, causes her to teleport then casts a spell again. The next teleport can prevent the Seraph from dealing successful attacks. Perhaps make this teleport effect available every few seconds (like 5- 10 seconds).\r\n\r\nOverall, nice synergy with the hero, but the only thing I have against it is the more ''brutal'' effects of its abilities.', '182.18.223.67', -1240277181, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
(202, 102, 201, 11, 'RE: The Night Angel', 0, 4, 'Alien@System', 1384878188, '[quote="DJackal"]\r\n- 50% slow could be lessened to something like 10 - 20%. The units are already pulled to her, so she doesn''t need a greater effect for positioning. You could have that 50% slow if you shrunk its duration to half a second to 1.5 seconds.\r\n [/quote]\r\n\r\nThe 50% slow only affects hero units, which aren''t moved by the chain, and the effect lasts only as long as the chain is attached, which is less than half a second. It ends once she has arrived, so the hero can continue running away pretty much immediately.\r\n\r\n[quote="DJackal"]\r\n- 20 seconds could be like 10 seconds or 15 seconds max.\r\n [/quote]\r\n\r\nYou''re probably right on that.\r\n\r\n[quote="DJackal"]\r\n- I find the DoT duration too long and the damage increase too high. Say 3 - 7 seconds with a 25 - 35% increase is fine.\r\n [/quote]\r\n\r\nThe description might be a bit confusing there. What I mean is, that whenever the Night Angel attacks, the DoT gets a bonus stack that increases its damage. After three second, that stack is removed again. If both Angel and Seraph hit a target, with an assumed Attack cd of 1 second (The standard warden attack is actually slightly slower, but is speeds up a bit with agility), you get on average 6 stacks at once, which means 7 times base DoT. And what I intend is that this Damage amount, 6 or 7 times the base DoT, is comparable to other DoTs. In other words, unless you constantly hit the target, you''re doing absolutely negilible scratch damage. The duration might be chosen a bit high, but again one has to consider that the Night Angel most likely won''t be able to use the timeframe 100% effectively.\r\n\r\n[quote="DJackal"]\r\n- The ultimate plays well, but I''m not sure with the teleport thing. It can really mess up her positioning. Say the Night Angel is attacking a unit, casts a spell, causes her to teleport then casts a spell again. The next teleport can prevent the Seraph from dealing successful attacks. Perhaps make this teleport effect available every few seconds (like 5- 10 seconds).\r\n [/quote]\r\n\r\nHadn''t considered double teleport, nice catch. Yeah, I think a short cooldown might be appropriate. On the other hand, you''re not meant to be able to easily direct the Seraph to a target you''re not targeting yourself.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n ', '77.179.211.198', 1303630790, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
(203, 102, 202, 11, 'RE: The Night Angel', 0, 78, 'DJackal', 1384943699, 'I partially blame myself for not fully understanding the abilities.\r\n\r\nThe DoT effect seems fine once explained, and the 50% slow on non-hero units is nicely done.', '182.18.223.69', -1240277179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', 0),
